Interface AppContextService<X extends AppContextService<X>>

  • Type Parameters:
    X - type service to be registered under
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConfigService, DatabaseService, ExecService, LoggerService, ResourceService, ServletService, SessionService<A>, TimerService
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConfigService, AbstractSessionService, BufferLoggerService, CachedConfigService, CleanupService, CommandLineLoggerService, CommonsLoggerService, CurrentTimeService, DataBaseConfigService, DataBaseHandlerService, DebugLoggerService, DefaultConfigService, DefaultDataBaseService, DefaultExecService, DefaultResourceService, DefaultServletService, DefaultTimerService, EmailLoggerService, GraphService, HttpService, JFreeGraphService, JNDIDatabaseService, Log4JLoggerService, MessageBundleService, MultiPartServletService, NavigationMenuService, OverrideConfigService, PrintLoggerService, RandomService, Servlet3MultiPartServletService, ServletConfigService, ServletContextConfigService, ServletEmailLoggerService, ServletResourceService, ServletSessionService, SimpleSessionService, SSLService

    public interface AppContextService<X extends AppContextService<X>>
    Interface for Services stored in an AppContext. Though the implementation of the services can form a class hierarchy the target services should not, as each one should be registered under a unique service. Service classes should be tagged with a PreRequisiteService to identify dependencies.
    Author:
    spb
